caption: Purchases Requiring Competitive Bidding Process ($35,000 or More)
created: 20260405120000000
modified: 20260405120000000
title: Policy3330(III)(1)
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Purchases of goods or general services, including high technology equipment, expected to involve an expenditure of $35,000 or more must be made by sealed competitive bid. As set forth below, such purchases in the amount of at least $15,000, but less than $35,000, may be awarded by the Superintendent of Schools or designee (collectively referred to as "Superintendent"). Such purchases in the amount of $35,000 or more must be approved by the Board.
